INSERT INTO fests VALUES (10,'Santa Barbara International Film Festival','Santa Barbara International Film Festival','','Santa Barbara','93103','1-805-963-0023','Santa Barbara International Film Festival','2064 Alameda Padre Serra, Suite 120','Santa Barbara','CA','93103','1-805-963 0023','1-805-962 2524','info@sbfilmfestival.org','http://www.sbfilmfestival.org','http://www.sbfilmfestival.org/images/logosmall.jpg','http://www.sbfilmfestival.org/images/2004FILMENTRYFORM.pdf','2002-08-11','2002-10-01','2002-11-21','2003-01-30','2003-02-08','Director&#039;s Filmography<br />\r\nSelf addressed, stamped envelope<br />\r\nPress kit','A 10-day event with over 40,000 attendees, including press, celebrities, distributors, film enthusiasts, members of the community and the local student population. Features over 75 film exhibitions, seminars, celebrity tributes, forums in new technology, galas and special events.','The Santa Barbara International Film Festival has added a Master Class Program for students in 2003. Through the Master Class Program, SBIFF hopes to provide an economical and educational forum, as well as foster education, by providing an open environment for discussionon on topics such as filmmaking, visual arts and current world and student issues. This program will consist of a combination of film screenings with question and answer sessions, showcase of student films, panel discussions with filmmakers and symposia and seminars. ','The Santa Barbara International Film Festival is a non-profit organization dedicated to celebrating the art of world cinema. Located on the American Riviera, the Festival offers a variety of film events thorughout the year, such as: film exhibitions, educational programs, celebrity tributes and forums in new technology.  ','','USA','Western','Films/Videos that have received national U.S. network television (including cable) or theatrical release prior to Festival are not eligible<br />\r\nStudent films must be 20 minutes or less. <br />\r\nFor preview purposes, 1/2&quot; VHS (NTSC) is preferred<br />\r\nMore than one entry may be submitted<br />\r\nTitles produced in languages other than English must have legible English subtitles<br />\r\n',NULL,'North America',1,'5 dollars off if you use withoutabox',1025,127,0,'Grand Jury Prize-International Competition<br />\r\nJury Prize for Best New American Director<br />\r\nLumina Award-Cinematography<br />\r\nBruce Corwin Award for Live Action Short<br />\r\nHuman Rights Award<br />\r\nAudience Award-Feature, Doc., Short<br />\r\n',2,'','Celebrating the art of world cinema','With a projected audience of over 40,000 viewing more than 150 screenings over its ten-day run, SBIFF attracts an affluent local and national consumer base, while maintaining strong ties with the entertainment industry in nearby Los Angeles. Daily symposiums discuss all aspects of film production.<br />\r\n','',1,'2003-07-23','CA');
