INSERT INTO fests VALUES (14,'Ann Arbor Film Festival','Michigan Theatre','','Ann Arbor','48104','734-668-8397','PO Box 8232','','Ann Arbor','MI','48107','1-734-995 5356','1-734-995 5396','info@aafilmfest.org','http://www.aafilmfest.org','http://www.aafilmfest.org/display/images/graphics/logo.gif','http://www.aafilmfest.org/filmmakers/entry_form/','0000-00-00','2002-12-01','0000-00-00','2003-03-11','2003-03-16','You must submit a brief 2-3 sentence statement (no more than 50 words) about your film for use in the festival program. ','The Ann Arbor Film Festival is the festival for independent and experimental film. Established in 1963, this internationally-renowned festival is the oldest of its kind in North America. Each year the festival attracts entries from filmmakers worldwide and screens more than 100 films before audiences 5,000 strong during six days in March. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Ann Arbor Film Festival fosters the growth of emerging and established filmmakers. It is the only venue in the midwest that solely exhibits independent 16mm and 35mm experimental film produced by film artists. The festival is open to films of all categories that demonstrate a high regard for film as an art form. Its mission is to provide a worldwide public forum for film screenings, to encourage and showcase independent &amp; experimental film artists, is to promote film as art, and to offer educational outreach. ','','The festival does not pride itself on fashioning money or stars, but over the years it has fostered its fair share of luminaries. We&#039;ve screened entries from such enterprising filmmakers as Brian DePalma, Andy Warhol, Lawrence Kasdan and George Lucas. Other notable entrants have included; Agnes Varda, Yoko Ono, Gus Van Sant, Barbara Hammer, Kenneth Anger, Sally Cruikshank and Will Vinton. ','','USA','North East','The Ann Arbor Film Festival only exhibits work at the festival on 16mm and 35mm. <br />\r\n',NULL,'North America',0,'',500,100,0,'The Ken Burns Best of the Festival Award - $3000 <br />\r\nThe EMPA Work Life Award - $1,200<br />\r\nTom Berman Award Most Promising Filmmaker - $1,000<br />\r\nScreening Committee&#039;s Choice for Narrative Integrity - $1,000<br />\r\nGus Van Sant Best Experimental Film Award <br />\r\nLawrence Kasdan Award Best Narrative Film<br />\r\nMichael Moore Award Best Documentary Film <br />\r\nChris Frayne Award Best Animated Film <br />\r\nPrix DeVarti Funniest Film <br />\r\nFilm Craft Lab/Kodak Award Best Cinematography - 35 or 16mm film stock + processing<br />\r\nGriot Editorial Best Editing Award - $500<br />\r\nLiberty Street Video Award Best Gay/Lesbian Film - $500<br />\r\nMichigan Vue Magazine Award Best Michigan Filmmaker - $500<br />\r\nAudiovisions/Amazing Audio Award (Best Sound Design) - $500<br />\r\nDoug Wandrei Award Best Lighting Design - $500<br />\r\nPeter Wilde Award Most Technically Innovative Film - $500<br />\r\nMarvin Felheim Award Special Jury Prize - $500<br />\r\nTio&#039;s Red Hot &amp; Spicy Award - $500<br />\r\nDetroit Filmmakers Coalition Award - $1500 in waived rental fees<br />\r\nIsabella Liddell Art Award - $400<br />\r\nHonorable Mentions -  $1,900<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n',2,'','The Ann Arbor Film Festival has showcased the works of independent and experimental 16mm film artists from around the world since 1963.','Post festival-week, the Festival Director selects a four-hour program of awarded and highlighted films for the Ann Arbor Film Festival Tour. As the founder of the traveling festival tour concept, the tour provides an excellent opportunity for filmmakers to gain additional audience and media exposure. It travels around the country March through December, to college classrooms and auditoriums, art theaters, and museums. The tour provides filmmakers the unique opportunity of having their work screened by audiences who, in some cities, only have access to this form of film art through the tour venue. The work of independent and experimental filmmakers is brought to thousands of new viewers each year.','',1,'2003-07-23','ME');
