INSERT INTO fests VALUES (27,'San Francisco International Lesbian And Gay Film Festival','Castro Threatre','','San Francisco','0','','Frameline','145 9th Street Suite 300','San Francisco','CA','94103','415 703 8650','1-415 861 1404','festival@frameline.org','http://www.frameline.org','','','0000-00-00','2002-01-02','0000-00-00','2002-01-01','2003-02-02','','The San Francisco International Lesbian &amp; Gay Film Festival is the oldest and largest event of its kind in the world, with annual audiences of over 84,000 applauding, whistling and cheering over 350 of the most innovative, creative and challenging queer films from 28 countries spanning the globe.  As of 2002, the SFILGFF now has the largest attendance of any film festival in California!','','The San Francisco International Lesbian &amp; Gay Film Festival is the world&#039;s largest and oldest event of its kind and has been referred to as the &quot;Gay Cannes&quot;.  Held over seventeen days the Festival screens over 350 works at three venues to audiences numbering more than 74,000  and it all takes place in one of the most beautiful and inviting cities in the world.  Seventeen days of films, panels and parties culminate with the Festivals Closing Night Premiere and Party on Lesbian/Gay Freedom Day.','','USA','Western','',NULL,'North America',0,'Sliding scale $15-25 based on fiscal need.',32,52,0,'',2,'We host multiple parties and events throughout the festival, including Opening Night, Centerpiece Party and Closing Night.','The San Francisco International Lesbian &amp; Gay Film Festival is dedicated to showcasing films that are by about and of interest to the LGBT community.','As the oldest and largest film festival of its kind, the SFILGFF is a unique opportunity to have your film seen at one of the largest film networking environments in California.','Extensive local and national coverage as well as the focus festival used by Variety to review  new LGBT films.',1,'2002-10-10','CA');
