INSERT INTO fests VALUES (1721,'Sample International Film Festival','Larchmont Playhouse','29 Larchmont Avenue','Larchmont','10538','(123) 456-7890','SIFF','123 Address Avenue','Mamaroneck','NY','12345','(987) 654-3210','(987) 654-3212','siff3@filmdevil.com','http://www.filmdevil.com','http://www.filmdevil.com/leftlogo.gif','','2002-01-03','2002-06-02','2002-09-02','2002-02-02','2002-02-04','VHS copy of film or video <br />\r\n$20 submission fee, made payable to Vinegar Hill Theater ($30 after Dec. 15)<br />\r\nSelf-addressed, stamped mailer for return of video <br />\r\nPublicity still and/or packet (optional)','Film Festival, funded by an unusual public/private partnership in Maryland, has two practical economic development goals: 1) to create a world class film festival centered in Baltimore, and 2) to bring filmmakers to Maryland as a way to encourage future production in the state. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur artistic goals are the foundation for everything we do. We recognize that there are many film festivals around the world, other good ones in and around Maryland, so the Maryland Film Festival is dedicated to adding something to what is already available. We are already establishing a unique personality. We want our festival audience to have a special experience. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe want a festival experience that is fun--celebrating the whole film culture, with no distinction between types of films. To us a great movie is a great movie. We realize this is a privilege the marketplace does not have. We strive to make Maryland Film Festival screenings distinct. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nAs a partner with the film community, we are building an annual event that will become a major fundraising vehicle for film preservation. <br />\r\n','The Maryland Film Festival, funded by an unusual public/private partnership in Maryland, has two practical economic development goals: 1) to create a world class film festival centered in Baltimore, and 2) to bring filmmakers to Maryland as a way to encourage future production in the state. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur artistic goals are the foundation for everything we do. We recognize that there are many film festivals around the world, other good ones in and around Maryland, so the Maryland Film Festival is dedicated to adding something to what is already available. We are already establishing a unique personality. We want our festival audience to have a special experience. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe want a festival experience that is fun--celebrating the whole film culture, with no distinction between types of films. To us a great movie is a great movie. We realize this is a privilege the marketplace does not have. We strive to make Maryland Film Festival screenings distinct. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nAs a partner with the film community, we are building an annual event that will become a major fundraising vehicle for film preservation. <br />\r\n','The Maryland Film Festival, funded by an unusual public/private partnership in Maryland, has two practical economic development goals: 1) to create a world class film festival centered in Baltimore, and 2) to bring filmmakers to Maryland as a way to encourage future production in the state. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nOur artistic goals are the foundation for everything we do. We recognize that there are many film festivals around the world, other good ones in and around Maryland, so the Maryland Film Festival is dedicated to adding something to what is already available. We are already establishing a unique personality. We want our festival audience to have a special experience. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe want a festival experience that is fun--celebrating the whole film culture, with no distinction between types of films. To us a great movie is a great movie. We realize this is a privilege the marketplace does not have. We strive to make Maryland Film Festival screenings distinct. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nAs a partner with the film community, we are building an annual event that will become a major fundraising vehicle for film preservation. <br />\r\n','','USA','North East','1.) Films must have been completed AFTER January 1, 2000. <br />\r\n2.) Running time for all feature length films must be no less than 60 minutes. Running time for all short films must be no more than 59 minutes.<br />\r\n3.) Films do not need to be a &quot;premiere,&quot; however, The Sample International Film Festival does emphasize World, North American, U.S. and Los Angeles premieres. Please contact our office before screening your film at other festivals and/or showcases. <br />\r\n4.) Films produced by a major motion picture studio are eligible. <br />\r\n5.) Foreign feature or short films submitted to The Sample International Film Festival must be SUBTITLED in English. <br />\r\n6.) Your submission tape should ONLY be VHS NTSC. All materials submitted will not be returned and become the property of The Sample International Film Festival. <br />\r\n7.) One official entry form must accompany each individual submission, along with the individual submission fee.',NULL,'North America',1,'Students receive a $5 discount.',1000,100,0,'Best Drama: $5000 Kodak film package<br />\r\nBest Documentary: $500<br />\r\nBest Student Film: $500<br />\r\nBest Experimental Film: $500<br />\r\nBest Animation: $500<br />\r\nMost Inspirational: $500',2,'This sleep town is usually, well, pretty sleep.  But when the Sample International Film Festival comes to town, we wake this place up.  Parties every night, open to all, drink specials for anyone with a ticket stub.  Always lots of fun!','The best environmental film festival in Larchmont!','Our quirky, foreign take on nature, and intelligent, critical view of environmentalism.','We get great press from the Westchester Daily and the Village Voice.  We always find a few attending filmmakers being interviewed for NPR and News 12.',1,'2003-07-21','NY');
