INSERT INTO fests VALUES (168,'African Diaspora Film Festival','ANTHOLOGY FILM ARCHIVES','','New York','10025','(212) 864-1760','ArtMattan Productions','535 Cathedral Parkway, Suite 14B','New York','NY','10025','(212) 864-1760','(212) 316-6020','info@africanfilm.com','http://nyadff.org/','','http://nyadff.org/entry%20form%20ADFF%202003.pdf','2003-06-30','2003-08-31','0000-00-00','2003-11-29','2003-12-11','1. A mixed set of black &amp; white and color stills from the film<br />\r\n2. Publicity materials and posters<br />\r\n3. A picture and short bio/filmography of the director<br />\r\n4. Any reviews of the film<br />\r\n5. A short synopsis (150 words or less) of the film in English<br />\r\n6. A VHS or PAL video cassette of your film for media review.','The African Diaspora Film Festival is dedicated to showcasing films that depict the richness and diversity of the experience of people of color all over the world.Includes over 50 films from 25 countries, Q&amp;As/panel discussions/closing concert.','','','','USA','North East','',NULL,'North America',0,'',0,0,0,'',0,'','In our reality, people from diverse races, nationalities and backgrounds come together to enjoy important cinematic works of creativity, intellectual expansion, identity, and equality. In this world there are no boundaries around people because they are embraced in a universal understanding of humanity. This is the element of commonality that weaves through this annual event of images from the African Diaspora.<br />\r\n','The ADFF is the only event of its kind that showcases the talent found in our communities. Our mission is to present these films to diverse audiences, redesign the Black cinema experience and strengthen the role of African descent directors in contemporary world cinema. In response to this mission, ADFF features the work of emerging and established filmmakers of color. Most important, ADFF distinguishes itself through its presentation of outstanding works that shine a different or comprehensive light on African Diaspora life and culture --no matter what the filmmakers race or nationality.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBy placing the spotlight on innovative films that would otherwise be ignored by traditional venues, the Festival will offer a unique platform for conveying African Diaspora artistic styles and craft in film. The ADFF is a bridge between diverse communities looking for works that cannot be found in other festivals and talented and visionary filmmakers and works that are part of the African Diaspora.<br />\r\n','',1,'2003-07-21','NY');
