INSERT INTO fests VALUES (581,'Canned by Southwest Film Fest','','','Austin','','','12100 Metric Blvd #1633','','Austin','TX','78758','713-447-4455','','cannedfilm@hotmail.com','http://www.cannedfilm.com','http://www.mxmentertainment.com/rollover.jpg','','0000-00-00','2003-02-01','0000-00-00','2003-03-28','2003-03-29','','Because of the tremendous success and exponential growth of South by Southwest, it seems the festival has grown unattainable for many of the low budget filmmakers who may not have the same resources as Peter Bogdanovich, Guillermo Del Toro, Ethan Hawke and Danny Glover, all major industry players whose latest films were exhibited last year. Even many of the narrative features and shorts had major stars attached, as actors (i.e.,Samuel L. Jackson, Frances McDormand), writers (i.e., Steve Martin) and directors. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nLast year, there were 170 films scheduled to be screened at the 2002 SXSW Film Festival, which means that at least some of the 1,830 rejected submissions were worthy films. We thought that many of these films should be seen. The goal of Canned! Film is to provide these rejected filmmakers an opportunity for a screening to promote their films. ','','','','USA','South West','Only films submitted to, but not selected by, the 2003 SXSW Film Festival are eligible for consideration. ',NULL,'North America',0,'',100,70,0,'',0,'','Chicks dig the underdog!','','',1,'2003-08-01','TX');
