INSERT INTO fests VALUES (748,'Canadian Film Centre&#039;s Worldwide Short Film Festival','Royal Ontario Museum Theatre','100 Queens Park','Toronto','','','Canadian Film Centre','2489 Bayview Avenue','Toronto, Ontario','Canada','0','416 445-1446 x815','1-416 445-9481','shortfilmfest@cdnfilmcentre.com','http://www.worldwideshortfilmfest.com','http://www.worldwideshortfilmfest.com/festival_info/images/film_can.jpg','','0000-00-00','2003-04-02','0000-00-00','2003-06-03','2003-06-08','','The Canadian Film Centre&#039;s Worldwide Short Film Festival presented by Sunlife Financial is an annual event featuring the best in Canadian and International shorts, competition screenings, retrospetives, galas, special scrennings, a Symposium and Marketplace.  The Festival&#039;s prize package is worth over $40,000 CDN.  Award-winning films in the Festival are eligible for consideration for the Genies and the Academy Awards.  ','','','','Canada','Ontario','',NULL,'North America',0,'',2100,200,0,'The Sun Life Financial Award for Best Canadian Short  -Generously offered by our presenting sponsor Sun Life Financial, this award consists of $25,000 cashone of the largest prizes for a short film in<br />\r\nthe world! <br />\r\nThe Kodak Award for Best Cinematography in a Canadian Short - Kodak will present the recipient of this award with a digital camera package valued at $4000. <br />\r\nThe C.O.R.E Digital Pictures Award for Best Animated Short - $5000 cash goes to the recipient of this prestigious award. <br />\r\nAward for Best Live-Action Short - A Sony digital video camcorder will be presented to the winner of this award. <br />\r\nAward for Best Experimental Short - A Sony digital video camcorder will be presented to the winner of this award. <br />\r\nAward for Best Documentary Short - A Sony digital video camcorder will be presented to the winner of this award. <br />\r\nVolkswagen Audience Choice Award - All shorts screening in the Festival are eligible for this award, which includes a cash prize of $5000 generously donated by VW. Fill out a ballot after the screening in the cinema lobby and you could win great prizes. ',2,'','The Worlds Best Shorts ','The growth of the Festival over the past two years has been tremendous. Toronto is a film-savvy city and a great place for screening shorts, and I know that our audience is catching on to the quality and originality that short films offer. The Festival is becoming a must-attend event on the cinematic calendar of residents, tourists and film fans alike.','',1,'2003-07-31','');
