INSERT INTO fests VALUES (776,'Mostra Internazionale del Cinema Libero','','','Bologna','','','Cineteca del Comune di Bologna','Via Riva di Reno 72','Bologna','Italy','40121','390-51-237 088','390-51-261 680','mailto:cinetecamanifestazioni1@comune.bologna.it','http://cinetecadibologna.it','http://cinetecadibologna.it/immagini/logo_cineteca.gif','','0000-00-00','0000-00-00','0000-00-00','2003-06-28','2003-07-05','','Festival of film restoration from international archives. The year 2003 marks the 50th anniversary of CinemaScope. Il Cinema Ritrovato will dedicate a section to its screen debut, from early tests to the pioneering experiments of Frenchman Henri Chrtien. We will look together at the glory years of the 1950s in American CinemaScope, a new technological feat celebrated with the slogan &quot;movies are better than ever&quot; (used as a weapon against the rising competition of television), and an aesthetic later celebrated by Rivette and Rohmer as &quot;the real avant-garde of its era&quot;; we will relive the splendid and creative three years from 53 to 56, marked by the luminous &quot;scope&quot; achievements of Nicholas Ray, Henry Hathaway, Otto Preminger, Samuel Fuller, Fritz Lang, and Richard Fleischer. A special section will bring us unique early scope films (the aspect ratio of 1:2:55, with magnetic stereophonic sound), starting of course with Henry Kosters The Robe (1953). Another fantastic series will showcase recently restored masterpieces of black and white CinemaScope, like Bitter Victory, Forty Guns, The Hustler.','','','','Italy','','',NULL,'Europe',0,NULL,0,0,0,'',1,'','Cinema larger than life','','',0,'2003-07-29','');
