INSERT INTO fests VALUES (787,'Cambridge Film Festival','','','Cambridge','','','Cambridge Arts Picturehouse','38-39 St Andrews Street','Cambridge','United Kingdom','CB2 3AR','44 1223 50 44 44','','festival@cambarts.co.uk','http://www.cambridgefilmfestival.org.uk/','http://www.picturehouses.co.uk/site/cinemas/cambridge/img/TalkToHer.gif','','0000-00-00','0000-00-00','0000-00-00','2003-07-10','2003-07-20','','Were celebrating our most popular Festival ever, with record audiences and nearly 50 UK premieres. The Festival team has been absolutely delighted by the overwhelming positive response weve had to this years event. Its been a hugely successful event, which the region is justifiably proud of. Its not often that Hollywood directors like Joel Schumacher and actors of Cate Blanchetts calibre visit regional festivals, but they came to Cambridge! We are proud to have presented an impressive and imaginative film programme to adventurous and enthusiastic audiences, and to have succeeded in putting Cambridge on a par with the most prestigious UK film festivals.','','','','United Kingdom','','',NULL,'Europe',0,NULL,0,150,0,'At the end of the Festival we&#039;ll select the very best review and award its writer the Fopp Top Critic award - including 30 to spend at Fopp on DVDs, invitations to all press screenings held at the Arts Picturehouse for one year, and a press pass to the 2004 Film Festival.',1,'','Screening the very best of current international cinema','The Cambridge Film Festival is one of the UK&#039;s most popular and influential British film festivals. It previously ran for 20 years from 1977 to 1996 before its successful re-launch in 2001 after a 5 year hiatus. Its original home was the much loved single-screen Arts Cinema in Cambridge city centre&#039;s Market Passage, where the Festival quickly developed from modest beginnings to become an important date in the international film festival calendar which would draw broad audiences from across the region and beyond. ','',0,'2003-07-31','');
