INSERT INTO fests VALUES (810,'Festival of European Films - Festival On Wheels','','','Ankara, Bursa, anakkale, Diyarbakr, Drama (Greece), Eskiehir, Gaziantep, stanbul, zmir, etc.','6700','90 312 466 34 84','Abay Kunanbay cad. Bilir sok. 20/13','Kavaklidere','Ankara','Turkey','6700','90 312 466 34 84','90 312 466 43 31','info@europeanfilmfestival.com','http://www.europeanfilmfestival.com','','http://www.europeanfilmfestival.com/entry.htm','0000-00-00','2003-08-01','0000-00-00','2003-10-03','2003-10-22',' Completed entry form <br />\r\n Credits of the film<br />\r\n Synopsis in English <br />\r\n Complete dialogue list / subtitle list in English<br />\r\n A VHS copy of the film with English subtitles<br />\r\n A Betacam selection from the film for TV promotion <br />\r\n Detailed bio-filmography of the director and the cast. <br />\r\n Stills from the film ( colour and black &amp; white ) <br />\r\n Recent photo of the director <br />\r\n Posters, brochures, press books, press reviews ','Can you imagine a festival on wheels, presenting 80-90 films while travelling 3000-4000 kilometres ? <br />\r\nThe Festival of European Films was first organised in 1995 to present remarkable Turkish and European films to the film lovers in various cities. Being a member of the European Coordination of Film Festivals, the Festival visits different cities to present its program during four weeks. Within the last eight years, the Festival visited Ankara, Bursa, anakkale, Diyarbakr, Drama (Greece), Eskiehir, Gaziantep, stanbul, zmir and Mersin. Traditionally, every year, the Turkish and foreign guests of the festival are hosted in Bursa, the old capital of the Ottoman Empire, near stanbul.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Festival invites filmmakers from different countries and introduces them to their Turkish counterparts to enable potential co-projects. It also contributes to the marketing of the festival films to commercial theatres and to TV companies.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEach year we screen 10-12 recent feature films and 40-50 recent short films. We also present classical films in Best of Europe, Love Films from Europe and Retrospectives sections. Each year, a retrospective of a Turkish director or classics from the Turkish cinema are in our program. <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis is the 9th fascinating gathering of the Festival of European Films. For eight years we have been sharing our excitement with film lovers and filmmakers. It is a real festive with colourful evenings, Turkish hospitality and the specialities of Turkish cuisine. How about watching films while wining and dining with fabulous people in an authentic atmosphere ? <br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis, we ensure, will be a unique experience to remember...<br />\r\n','','','','Turkey','','Must be a European film.',NULL,'Europe',0,'',0,0,0,'Short Film Audience Award of 1000',2,' It is a real festive with colourful evenings, Turkish hospitality and the specialities of Turkish cuisine. How about watching films while wining and dining with fabulous people in an authentic atmosphere ? ','The Festival aims to introduce a distinguished selection of European Films to the Turkish audience and to give an ardent desire for a nation-wide distribution. ','Can you imagine a festival on wheels, presenting 80-90 films while travelling 3000-4000 kilometres ? ','',1,'2003-07-21','');
