INSERT INTO fests VALUES (899,'Banff Mountain Film Festival','','','Banff','','403-762-6369','Mountain Culture, The Banff Centre','Box 1020, 107 Tunnel Mountain Drive','Banff','Alberta, Canada','T&amp;L 1H5','403-762-6369','403-762-6277',' banffmountainfilms@banffcentre.ca','http://www.banffcentre.ca/CMC','http://www.banffcentre.ca/mountainculture/images/logos/bclogo.gif','http://www.banffcentre.ca/mountainculture/forms/film/','0000-00-00','2003-08-08','0000-00-00','2003-11-04','2003-11-09','Entries MUST be accompanied by two VHS copies. All video<br />\r\nsubmissions, except HDTV productions, will be retained by the<br />\r\nfestival for pre-selection, on-demand and archival purposes.<br />\r\nProduction attributes should conform to typical broadcast<br />\r\nstandards and include:<br />\r\n 90 seconds of leader which include black, SMPTE colour bars, and<br />\r\nblack with either +4dbm (analog) or -20dbfs (digital) audio tone<br />\r\nreference signals.<br />\r\n 7.5 IRE Pedestal Black (preferred).<br />\r\n Maximum 105% IRE clipped peak whites.<br />\r\n Program start commences on the timecode hour<br />\r\n Program tail of two minutes of black.<br />\r\n Digital content should be submitted with 48K audio and have peak<br />\r\nwhites which don&#039;t exceed 105% IRE.','The Banff Mountain Film Festival is an annual, competitive, international event bringing the best films on mountains and their spirit of adventure to the mountain town of Banff, Alberta. The festival provides an opportunity for filmmakers to meet and exchange ideas in a relaxed environment through the provision of seminars, on-demand screening facilities and social gatherings.','','Last year, filmmakers from 31 countries entered over 263 films in the 2002 Banff competition. Many of the films had an opportunity to tour worldwide to an audience of over 150,000 serious mountain and adrenaline film junkies, through the Banff Mountain Film Festival World Tour.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter spending time with Yosemite Camp 4 climbers in 1998,<br />\r\n','Mountain sports and the outdoors','Canada','Alberta','',NULL,'North America',0,'',350,263,0,'Grand Prize $4,000 cash prize<br />\r\n$2,000 cash prize for each of the following:<br />\r\nAlpine Club of Canada Award for Best Film on Climbing<br />\r\nBest Film on Mountain Sports<br />\r\nBest Film on Mountain Environment<br />\r\nBest Film on Mountain Culture<br />\r\nBest Short Mountain Film (15 minutes or less)<br />\r\nBest Feature-length Mountain Fiction Film<br />\r\nPeoples Choice Award',2,'','Have You Always Dreamed of Seeing Your Name on the Big Screen?','The Banff Mountain Film Festival, presented by National Geographic and Dunham Bootmakers, brings you the worlds best mountain films, videos, and speakers. Experience the adventure of climbing, mountain expeditions, remote cultures, and the worlds last great wild places  all brought to life on the big screen.<br />\r\nAfter 28 years, the Banff Mountain Film Festival has a proven track record as the world&#039;s largest and one of the most prestigious mountain film festivals. The Banff Mountain Film Festival and the festival world tour reach a live audience of more than 150,000 people in over 30 countries. Selected festival films will have the opportunity to be featured in Banff Mountain Film Festival network<br />\r\ntelevision series.','',1,'2003-07-25','');
