INSERT INTO fests VALUES (947,'Buster Copenhagen International Children&#039;s Film Festival','','','Copenhagen','','','C/O The Danish Film Institute','Vognmagergade 10','Copenhagen K','Denmark','1120','+45 33743545','+4533743435','anes@dfi.dk','http://www.busterfilm.dk','http://www.busterfilm.dk/eng/business/undermenu/images/business_12.jpg','http://www.busterfilm.dk/downloads/pdf/buster_2002_entry_form.pdf','0000-00-00','2003-06-10','0000-00-00','2003-09-29','2003-10-05','','This year, BUSTER has made a giant step towards becoming a large, international film festival. From this year on, BUSTER hosts the annual, Nordic meeting for childrens film professionals, New Nordic Childrens Film, a section of the festival that will attract more international guests. BUSTER has grown into a large, international film festival with a number of sub categories and sections, that has a lot to offer both children, adolescents, adults, schools, and the film business.','','2003 is BUSTERs fourth year, and in those four years, the festival has grown extensively in both attendance and attention from the media and from the business. From 2001 to 2002 alone, attendance rose by more than 100%, so last years festival saw more than 18.000 seats filled at BUSTER screenings.','','Denmark','','',NULL,'Europe',0,'',0,0,0,'Feature films:<br />\r\nNordic Film Funds Award: Best BUSTER 2003: Dkr 50.000 / Euro 7.000<br />\r\nBUSTERs Grand Prix: Dkr 50.000 / Euro 7.000<br />\r\n<br />\r\nShort films:<br />\r\nPolitikens Short Film Prize: Dkr 15.000 / Euro 2.000<br />\r\nBUSTERs Short Film Prize: Dkr 15.000 / Euro 2.000<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDuring New Nordic Childrens Film there will also be an award for best Nordic childrens feature, and an award for the most innovative new Nordic short film or documentary.<br />\r\n',2,'','Large and highly respected international children and youth film festival','For the first time this October, New Nordic Childrens Film will make BUSTER the center for dialogue, exchange and collaboration across borders between the children and youth film business from Sweden, Norway, Iceland, Finland, and Denmark. And just as importantly, New Nordic Childrens Film will also present the Nordic children and youth films to the rest of the world.','',1,'2003-07-31','');
