INSERT INTO fests VALUES (971,'Alpe Adria Cinema Film Festival Trieste','','piazza Duca degli','Trieste','34100','+39 040 365119','A. Percavassi, Festival Director','Via S. Rocco 1','Trieste','','34121','+39 040 311153','+39 040 311993','aac@spin.it','http://www.spin.it/alpeadriacinema/','','http://www.spin.it/alpeadriacinema/download/pdf/Regulations15.pdf','0000-00-00','2003-10-31','0000-00-00','2004-01-15','2004-01-22','The owners of SELECTED films must allow the following advertising and<br />\r\npromotional material, to reach our offices by November 15th, 2003:<br />\r\n- 5 posters;<br />\r\n- 20 b/w and colour photographs of film-scenes;<br />\r\n- 30 press books;<br />\r\n- Synopsis of the film;<br />\r\n- Cast and credits;<br />\r\n- Directors biography;<br />\r\n- Directors complete filmography (indicating the original titles);<br />\r\n- Directors brief statement on his/her film;<br />\r\n- Dialogue list;<br />\r\n- Dialogue list in the subtitles language;<br />\r\n- A VHS 100% faithful to the copy presented at the festival, for the electronic subtitling;<br />\r\n- A Betacam tape with the film excerpts (3 max) for promotional use.','The 15th Trieste Film Festival is articulated into the following sections:<br />\r\nSelezione Ufficiale - Concorso Internazionale Lungometraggi (Official Selection - International Feature<br />\r\nFilms Competition) and &quot;Concorso Internazionale Cortometraggi&quot; (&quot;International Short Films<br />\r\nCompetition&quot;) will present a selection of the most recent productions in 35mm and 16mm,<br />\r\nmainly focusing on those films that feature originality and linguistic innovation, as well as on<br />\r\nthe productions concentrated on particular aspects and problems of the society and culture of<br />\r\nthe country of origin.<br />\r\nSezione Immagini (Images Section) will present a selection of films and audiovisual material<br />\r\nfeaturing investigation into the language of cinema, the stages and methods involved in story<br />\r\ntelling with images, and experimentation including the use of new technologies. The section<br />\r\nwill be articulated into the following programmes: feature-length films, short and medium<br />\r\nlength films; documentaries and cartoons; special interest material, fragments, screen tests and<br />\r\ndirector&#039;s cuts, as well as television work.<br />\r\nRetrospective and Monographic Sections','','','','Italy','','',NULL,'Europe',0,'',0,0,0,'An International Jury composed of 3 figures of various nationalities from the world of<br />\r\ncinema and the arts in general will award a prize of 5,000 Euros, the TRIESTE PRIZE, offered<br />\r\nby the Municipality of Trieste, to the Best Feature Film in competition, to be divided equally<br />\r\nbetween director and producer. Another jury of 3 figures of various nationalities from the<br />\r\nworld of cinema will assign a prize of 1,500 Euros to the Best Short Film in competition, offered<br />\r\nby the Mediterranean Laboratory Foundation of Naples.',2,'','The main purpose of the Trieste Film Festival<br />\r\nis to promote information, debate and mutual cooperation among the operators of the audiovisual<br />\r\nproduction industry and in particular of feature films in Central and Eastern Europe.','','',1,'2003-07-21','');
