INSERT INTO fests VALUES (1134,'Week With The Masters Animation Celebration','Technopark Campus','','Trivandrum','695','91-471-416-928','731-735 Nila','Technopark Campus','Trivandrum, Kerala','India','695581','91-471-416-928','91-471-416-954','toonz@toonzanimationindia.com','http://www.toonzanimationindia.com','','','0000-00-00','2003-08-15','0000-00-00','2003-11-04','2003-11-08','--Biography of Director<br />\r\n--One Photo (black &amp; white or color in print, slide or digital form) of Director<br />\r\n--Prints, slides or digital images from the film (minimum three)<br />\r\n--Text of dialogue or commentaries with English translation (if your film is in a<br />\r\n--language other than English and does not have English subtitles).','The competition, the only one of its kind in India, provides a stage to showcase talents within Asia and give them international exposure. Entries are open to independent animation artists, including students from India and other Southeast Asian countries. The Animation Contest forms the cornerstone of the &#039;Week With The Masters&#039; celebrations. ','Special student section for films less than 30 minutes long.','','','India','','Only works completed after 15 August 2001 can be entered. Entries must be produced by citizens or residents of India or other Asian countries. The competition is open to independent and student-made short films up to 30 minutes in length, as well as commercials up to two minutes in length.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nStudent films must be made as part of course requirments for a recognized post-secondary (college-level) educational institution.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIndependent films, for purposes of this competition, are productions made for artistic rather than strictly commercial purposes, and are those in which the director has principal control.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTelevision and theatrical commercials include productions made for advertising and promotional purposes, including public service announcements and television station I.D.s.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nProductions which are part of a television series are not eligible for competition. Films made by staff members of Toonz Animation India Pvt. Ltd. are also not eligible.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAll entries must be animated in whole or in part. Live-action films may be entered if they contain a significant animation component.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn all cases, the pre-selection committee is the sole determinant of eligibility for the competition.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n',NULL,'Asia',1,'',0,0,0,'The best entry will receive the coveted Master&#039;s Trophy and the Grand Prize of $2,000 and the category prize of $1,000 will be awarded to the best entry in each category. The jury may also award additional prizes as they see fit.',2,'','Animation Magazine, the most widely read publication in the international animation industry, has selected TOONZ Animation India Ltd., as one among the top 10 companies to watch in animation.','The Week With The Masters Animation Celebration is organized by Toonz Animation India Pvt. Ltd. and is dedicated to the art of animation. The emphasis is on fun, camaraderie and one-on-one interaction with animation masters.','',1,'2003-08-04','');
