INSERT INTO fests VALUES (1152,'Blue Sky International Film Festival','','','Las Vegas','','','BSIFF','4185 Paradise Rd. Suite 2009','Las Vegas','NV','89109','702-737-3313','','info@bsiff.com','http://www.bsiff.com','http://www.bsiff.com/bsifftitle.gif','http://www.bsiff.com/form7-31-03.pdf','0000-00-00','2003-07-31','0000-00-00','2003-09-25','2003-09-28','Press kit','Since that time, BSIFF has become the best source for independent and world cinema in Las Vegas. Every year BSIFF showcases a variety of films from such countries as the United States, Canada, Mexico, Brazil, Japan, Korea, Singapore, India, Australia, New Zealand, England, France and Germany.','','','','USA','Western','Films must have been completed after January 1, 2002.<br />\r\nForeign films must be in English or have English sub-titles.',NULL,'North America',0,'',0,0,0,'The BSIFF Director&#039;s Award was created to aid in a filmmaker&#039;s next feature film project. It is a post-production gift, donated be the Seattle Post Affiliates, valued at over $12,000 in post services.',1,'','The premier provider of award-winning, independent and world cinema in Las Vegas.','The Las Vegas Filmmaker Forum is a gathering point for independent filmmakers and producers. A place where information is transacted face-to-face and where each member gets connected on a personal level. Behind the forum walls the richest and deepest content is delivered, creating an interactive experience for all who attend. At the end of each session, filmmakers walk away with a new look at the industry and with a sense that they have gained a valuable insight into their own business. Past presenters include: Richard Krevlon, David Russell and Louise Levinson.','',1,'2003-07-29','NV');
INSERT INTO fests VALUES (1153,'Black Filmmakers Hall of Fame, Inc.','','','Oakland','','','410 Fourteenth Street','','Oakland','CA','94612','510 465-0804','510 839 9858','BFHFINC@AOL.COM','http://www.blackfilmmakershall.org','http://www.blackfilmmakershall.org/images/Gold.gif','http://www.blackfilmmakershall.org/03Eform.htm','2003-06-30','2003-07-15','0000-00-00','2003-08-01','2003-08-01','A synopsis of the entry. Please limit to one paragraph,<br />\r\nResume &amp; photo of qualifying person - producer, writer, director, etc.,<br />\r\nA still from the production and/or filmmaker to help in publicizing screening events<br />\r\n','Black Filmmakers Hall of Fame, Inc. (BFHFI) is a non-profit organization dedicated to influencing Black images portrayed in film and television through education, the nurturing of current independent filmmakers, and the preservation of contributions by African American artists both before and behind the camera. ','','','','USA','Western','',NULL,'North America',0,'',0,0,0,'Black Filmmakers Hall of Fame, Inc. has a two-tier judging process. The 1st Level Judges select the winning projects in each Category.  The Category Winners are forwarded to a Blue Ribbon Panel from which they select the overall competition winners.  Black Filmmakers Hall of Fame, Inc.s staff reserves the right to assemble an Intermediate Professional Panel to assist in the selection of projects being forwarded to the Blue Ribbon Panel. <br />\r\n<br />\r\n1st Prize $1500<br />\r\n2nd Prize $750<br />\r\n3rd Prize $500<br />\r\n',2,'','','Film and television--they are two of media&#039;s most powerful resources that have provided us with the ability to manifest our dreams. For 26 years, Black Filmmakers Hall of Fame, Inc. has been a driving force in acknowledging the richness within the lives of African Americans. From Oscar Micheaux to Sidney Poitier to Spike Lee... ','',1,'2003-07-28','CA');
