INSERT INTO fests VALUES (1662,'Argos Festival','','','Brussels','','','Brice Muylle','Werfstraat 13 rue du Chantier','Brussels','Belgium','1000','+32 02 229 00 03','+32 02 223 73 31','festival@argosarts.org','http://www.argosarts.org/festival/2003/index.html','http://www.argosarts.org/festival/2002/images/argosFestival_part_1.gif','http://www.argosarts.org/festival/2003/entryForm.doc','0000-00-00','2003-06-15','0000-00-00','2003-10-17','2003-10-17','a short biography','The festival offers a stage to all kinds of artistic forms of expression in the realm of audio-visual media. Next to an extensive international programmation, the argos festival will, as usual, give an overview of recent Belgian audiovisual productions.','','','','Belgium','','No international (non-Belgian) entries are accepted.<br />\r\nFeature films, narrative short films, conventional documentaries and documentations of video installations are not accepted.',NULL,'Europe',0,'',0,0,0,'',0,'','The festival with a Belgian Focus','Spread across six locations  argos, Cinema Nova, the Film Museum, Matrix Art Project, Recyclart and Ancienne Belgique  this annual event on artistic audiovisual productions reveals itself as the largest in Belgium. In 2002, the festivals interdisciplinary programme again gnaws away at the boundaries: film, video, new media, performance, the fine arts and music move alongside, but also through one another.','',1,'2003-07-24','');
