INSERT INTO fests VALUES (1668,'Biennale Cinema Ragazzi','Palazzo del Cinema','','Lido di Venezia','','','','','Lido di Venezia','Italy','','+39041 5218878','+39041 5227539','cinema@labiennale.org','http://biennale.tiscali.it/en/cinema/','http://biennale.tiscali.it/it/img/logo-biennale.gif','','0000-00-00','2003-06-16','0000-00-00','2003-04-27','2003-09-06','','The Festival aims to encourage, in an atmosphere of freedom and tolerance, the awareness and the promotion of all aspects of world cinema as an art, as entertainment and as an industry. In addition to the sections mentioned in the following paragraphs, the Festival program will include tributes to outstanding personalities as well as retrospectives, as a contribution to a better understanding of the history of cinema.','','As part of the Festival, the &quot;Venice Screenings&quot; will provide producers and distributors with screening and market facilities to ease their contacts with buyers and promoters. Participation at the &quot;Venice Screenings&quot; is subject to separate regulations.','','Italy','','',NULL,'Europe',0,'',0,0,0,'There are two main competition sections, each with a separate jury. The first is &quot;Venezia 60&quot; with the Gold and Silver Lion awards, the second is the &quot;Upstream&quot; section with the San Marco prize endowed with 50&#039;000 Euro. Although the borderline between both competitions is subject to appreciation, it is generally recognized that &quot;Venezia 60&quot; is more characterized by mainstream films, while &quot;Upstream&quot; is more concentrated on presenting innovative films and alternative filmmaking.',1,'','The awareness and the promotion of all aspects of world cinema as an art','Federico Fellini once said that for a film director, &quot;entering the Film Palace of the Venice Film Festival, was like passing a final exam.&quot; This is the place where film festivals were invented. The Mostra, inaugurated in 1932, is the oldest festival in the world and as part of the Biennale of Venice of course is renowned for its particular sensitivity to film as an Art. Besides this it is ideally scheduled to open the fall theatrical season with the prestigious setting offered by the surrounding town of Venice with its century-long history.','',1,'2003-07-25','');
